It came from a millionaire
I looked up to as a kid.

4
00:00:07,110 --> 00:00:09,690
After overhearing him
talk about investing,

5
00:00:09,690 --> 00:00:11,070
I wanted to get involved.

6
00:00:11,070 --> 00:00:12,570
But as a complete beginner,

7
00:00:12,570 --> 00:00:14,490
I didn't know where to start.

8
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:17,400
So I asked him, "How do
I pick the right stocks

9
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,360
to invest in?"

10
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:20,737
His answer was very simple.

11
00:00:20,737 --> 00:00:23,310
"Treat it like finding a girlfriend."

12
00:00:23,310 --> 00:00:25,440
This is quite a clever way to look at it.

13
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:27,510
Because when you buy a share in a company,

14
00:00:27,510 --> 00:00:29,730
you actually become a part owner.

15
00:00:29,730 --> 00:00:33,240
This is like a partnership
between you and the company,

16
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:35,010
and just like a relationship

17
00:00:35,010 --> 00:00:38,520
you wanna make sure it's
happy, long, and successful.

18
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:40,920
But look, I'm not gonna pretend
that there's a crystal ball

19
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:42,420
that can tell you when to buy a stock

20
00:00:42,420 --> 00:00:43,890
before it rockets in value

21
00:00:43,890 --> 00:00:46,470
like most of the fake gurus online.

22
00:00:46,470 --> 00:00:49,260
However, there are certainly
a few things you can do

23
00:00:49,260 --> 00:00:51,573
to tip the odds in your favor.

24
00:00:51,573 --> 00:00:53,550
(light upbeat music)

25
00:00:53,550 --> 00:00:55,020
When you're looking for a partner,

26
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:57,210
you need to have a strategy in mind.

27
00:00:57,210 --> 00:00:59,700
Are you gonna shower them
with gifts like a simp

28
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,710
or treat them mean to keep them keen?

29
00:01:01,710 --> 00:01:03,150
You'll get very different results

30
00:01:03,150 --> 00:01:05,490
depending on which strategy you choose,

31
00:01:05,490 --> 00:01:07,320
